caption: As a San Diegan I can quickly become a critic when it comes to Mexican food.  I can't believe I had not tried this spot sooner. I pass it all the time. Absolutely delish. Totally reminds me of home. The food was delivered hot and got here super fast.  The mole is the best I have had in Brooklyn so far. Can't wait to try more items on the menu!

Didn't even try to the food but don't order from there. Place is a joke. The owner of this place should reconsider his employees.

This baja californian expat feels nostalgia at this authentic Mexican spot in the neighborhood. Menu items made fresh! Tacos were very good. Chorizo was salty, great to pair with the carne asada.  Plenty of seafood options (shrimp and fish) on the menu. No fish tacos tho.  Chill place. Run by nice folks.  Good place to meet up with friends. Right across the street from Kings Highway (N) station entrance and in front of B82 bus stops.
